# Project Patterns

## Stack
- React 19 + TypeScript (strict) + Vite 7
- Inline CSS (`style={{...}}`) for section-level components — NOT Tailwind classes
- Tailwind utilities are reserved for `src/components/ui/` (shadcn primitives only)
- GSAP + ScrollTrigger for scroll animations
- Three.js for WebGL (Hero shader background)
- i18n via `useI18n()` hook — all user-facing strings must go through `t('key')`

## File Structure
```
src/
  sections/   # Full-page sections: Hero, Works, Capabilities, etc.
  components/
    ui/        # Reusable shadcn/Radix primitives ONLY
  data/        # Static data (gyms.ts)
  i18n/        # Translations (translations.ts) + context (I18nContext.tsx)
  hooks/       # Custom hooks (use-mobile.ts)
  lib/         # Tiny utilities (utils.ts)
```

## TypeScript
- No `any` — use `unknown` + type guards
- Prefer `interface` for component props, `type` for unions and aliases
- No non-null assertions (`!`) unless the value is provably present
- Cast env vars explicitly: `import.meta.env.VITE_X as string | undefined`

## Styling Conventions
- `clamp(min, preferred, max)` for responsive font sizes and spacing
- Responsive grids: `repeat(auto-fit, minmax(min(100%, Xpx), 1fr))`
- Validate layouts at 375 px, 768 px, and 1280 px before shipping
- For conditional mobile styles, use the `useIsMobile()` hook

## Performance
- Lazy-load below-the-fold sections with `React.lazy()` + `<Suspense>`
- Cap per-chunk size to < 300 KB gzipped
- Use `Math.min(window.devicePixelRatio, 2)` for canvas pixel ratio (already standard in project)
- GSAP contexts (`gsap.context()`) must be cleaned up in the `useEffect` return

## Environment Variables
- All client-side vars: `import.meta.env.VITE_*` (type: `string | undefined`)
- GitHub Actions sets secrets as env vars; `.env.local` is for local dev only

## Deploy
- Push to `main` → GitHub Actions → Vite build → `gh-pages` branch
- `vite.config.ts` sets `base: '/team-mas-bjj/'` only when `GITHUB_ACTIONS=true`
- `public/404.html` handles SPA routing on GitHub Pages (spa-github-pages technique)
